  "prompt": "Is there any app like Shazam to get the chord tabs when hearing a song?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps and tools available that can help you identify chord tabs when hearing a song, similar to how Shazam identifies songs. Some popular ones include:\n\n1. **Chordify:** Chordify is a web-based service and mobile app that automatically recognizes and displays chords from any song you play through it. It works with YouTube, SoundCloud, and other music sources.\n\n2. **Ultimate Guitar:** Ultimate Guitar's app has a feature called \"Tonebridge\" which can analyze music and show you the chords and tabs for various songs. It's a popular app among guitarists.\n\n3. **Songsterr:** Songsterr provides a large library of guitar, bass, and drum tabs. While it doesn't automatically detect chords from audio, it offers high-quality tabs and can be a useful resource for musicians.\n\n4. **Yousician:** Yousician is an interactive music learning app that provides tabs and chord charts for songs. It includes a feature that listens to you play and gives feedback, though it's primary focus is on learning rather than instant chord tab recognition.\n\nThese tools can be very helpful for musicians looking to learn new songs and understand their structure.",
